INSERT INTO `en_articles` (`article_id`, `hits`, `time`, `author_id`, `title`, `full`, `keywords`, `description`, `editor_id`, `editing_end`, `seo_link`) VALUES
(1, 64, 1337541493, 1, 'Czech Republic Spa Holidays - Health Care - Beauty Treatments', '<h1>Czech Spa Holidays.com is an independent travel agency specializing in organizing health and beauty holidays in mineral and thermal water Spa and Wellness Resorts of the Czech Republic.</h1>\n<div class="material_shot">\n<table class="material_1" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_title">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_imege"><img src="/images/pictures/1.gif" alt="COMPLEX TREATMENTS" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_text">Why visit the Czech Republic for health and beauty holidays? Spending your holidays in the Czech Republic taking full advantage of health &amp; beauty, wellness and relaxation programmes that the Czech Republic mineral Spa and Wellness hotels have to offer is becoming more and more popular.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class="material_2" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_title">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_imege"><img src="/images/pictures/2.gif" alt="REGENERATION PROGRAMMES FOR CHILDREN" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_text">Located in central Europe, the Czech Republic is blessed with mineral and thermal springs that have curative, therapeutic, relaxation effect on your body and soul. The most famous and visited thermal Spa and Wellness Resorts in the Czech Republic are: Karlovy Vary, Klimkovice, Lednice, Luhacovice, Bludov, Lesenik, Lazne Belohrad, Lipova Lazne, Vraz and many more.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class="material_1" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_title">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_imege"><img src="/images/pictures/3.gif" alt="WELLNESS ANTISTRESS AND RELAXATION PROGRAMMES" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_text">The mineral springs have been used in the Czech Republic for health and beauty treatments since 14 century . The in-depth understanding of mineral and thermal waters and the effect they have on ourimmune system, digestive system, cardio-vascular systems, stress levels, and our body as whole allowed mineral Spa and Wellness Hotels of the Czech Republic to tailor programmes and procedures that are effective.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_link">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class="cl">&nbsp;</div>\n<table class="material_1" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_title">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_imege"><img src="/images/pictures/4.gif" alt="PAMPERING FOR WOMEN" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_text">Spa and Wellness Resorts offer a wide range of beauty treatments that have an unforgettable effect on your body and soul. They also offer a wide range of health procedures that are beneficial for your over all health as well as for specific areas such as immune system, stress level, improving your digestive system, cardio-vascular system, etc.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_link">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class="material_2" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_title">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_imege"><img src="/images/pictures/5.gif" alt="SENIOR PROGRAMMES" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_text">Another good reason for visiting the Czech Republic for health and beauty holidays is the fact that it is very affordable. Wellness and Relaxation stays carefully crafted by Spa and Wellness Resorts in the Czech Republic give you a lot for your money. The Czech Republic is culturally very rich country, with lots palaces, monuments, and castles to visit. Local cuisine, warm welcome of local people will greatly contribute to the fact that you will spend unforgettable health and beauty holidays in one of the most popular Spa and Wellness Resorts of Europe.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_link">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class="material_1" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_title">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_imege"><img src="/images/pictures/6.gif" alt="SPA BEGINNERS" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_text">And yet another good reason for visiting the Czech Republic for health and beauty stays or wellness and relaxation programmes is the fact that it is easily accessible. The Czech Republic located in Central Europe and budget airlines fly frequently to Prague, Brno, Karlovy Vary. Spa and Wellness Hotels can also offer you a transfer from the neighboring airports such as Vienna or Bratislava.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="m_link">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class="cl">\n<h1>So, do not think twice and book online your wellness and relaxation stays in the Czech Republic, and have your best health and beauty holiday in Europe. Booking online with Czech Spa Holidays.com will be available soon.</h1>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Spa, health, beauty, mineral water, Wellness Resorts, Czech Republic, beauty holidays, Spa hotels, thermal springs, Karlovy Vary, Lednice, Luhacovice, Bludov, Lesenik, Lazne Belohrad, Lipova Lazne, Vraz, immune system, digestive system, cardio-vascular systems, stress level,  affordable holidays, deals, offers', 'Czech Spa Holidays.com is an independent travel agency specializing in organizing health and beauty holidays in mineral and thermal water Spa and Wellness Resorts of the Czech Republic.', NULL, NULL, ''),
(2, 1, 1337593250, 1, 'Useful Info', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="#Overview">Overview</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Time">Time</a></p>\n<p><a href="#Embassies">Embassies and Consulates</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Visas">Visas</a>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="#Phone">Important Phone Numbers </a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Safety">Safety</a></p>\n<p><a href="#Climate">Climate and Weather</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Money">Money</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="#Comunications">Communications </a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Tipping">Tipping</a></p>\n<p><a href="#Holidays">Public Holidays</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Smoking">Smoking</a></p>\n<p><a href="#Customs">Local Customs</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Language">Language</a></p>\n<p><a href="#Vaccination">Vaccinations</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Insurance2">Insurance</a></p>\n<p><a href="#Phrasebook">Phrasebook</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="#Electricity">Electricity</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Overview"></a>Overview</strong></p>\n<p>The Czech Republic is a landlocked country in Central Europe with a population of 10.5 million people. Prague is the capital and the largest city in the Czech Republic, with 1.3 million inhabitants. It is a pluralist multi-party parliamentary representative democracy, a member of the EU, NATO, the OECD, the OSCE, the Council of Europe and the Visegrad Group.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a name="Embassies"></a><strong>Embassies and Consulates</strong></p>\n<p>Foreign Embassies in the Czech Republic:</p>\n<p>UK: Thunovska 14, 118 00 Prague 1; Tel: +420 257 402 111 Fax: +420 257 402 296</p>\n<p>Germany: Vla&scaron;sk&aacute; 19, 118 01 Prague 1 (Mal&aacute; Strana); Tel: +420 257 113 111 Fax: +420 257 534 056</p>\n<p>Russia: nam. Pod Kastany 1, Praha 6 &ndash; Bubenec; Tel: +420 233 374 100 Fax: +420 233 377 235</p>\n<p>Austria: Viktora Huga 10, 15115 Prague; Tel: +420 257 090 511 Fax: +420 257 316 045</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Phone"></a>Important Phone Numbers: </strong></p>\n<p><strong>112 emergency calls</strong> (this number works throughout the whole of Europe and includes universal medical aid, the police and the fire brigade &ndash; but it may not necessarily work on older mobile telephones without SIM cards)</p>\n<p><strong>150 - Fire Brigade</strong></p>\n<p><strong>155 - Ambulance</strong></p>\n<p><strong>158 &ndash; Police</strong></p>\n<p><strong>156</strong> - <strong>Municipal Police (limited authority, resolve smaller, local problems)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Climate"></a>Climate and Weather </strong></p>\n<p>The Czech Republic has a temperate continental climate, with relatively hot summers and cold and snowy winters. The temperature difference between summer and winter is relatively high, due to the landlocked geographical position.</p>\n<p>The coldest months are usually December, January and February with temperatures, at times, going up to -20 &deg;C in some areas.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>During March, April and May, the temperature usually increases rapidly, especially during April, when the temperature and weather tends to vary widely during the day.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The warmest months are June, July, August. Especially in the last decade temperatures above +30 &deg;C during the summer are not unusual.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Autumn is usually dry and warm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Comunications"></a>Communications</strong></p>\n<p>Internet:</p>\n<p>Internet is widely available in hotels and internet cafes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Phone Calls:</p>\n<p>The international access code for the Czech Republic is +420.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The outgoing code is 00 followed by the relevant country code.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The easiest way to make calls is to use the phone at your hotel room; however, this route is the most expensive because of pricey surcharges.&nbsp; It is therefore a lot cheaper to use the public telephone boxes. Phone cards are widely available from newsagent.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The local mobile phone operators use GSM networks and have roaming agreements with all major international operators, except those in the USA.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Holidays"></a>Public Holidays</strong></p>\n<p>Czech Republic Public Holidays for 2012:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1 January - New Year''s Day</p>\n<p>9 April - Easter</p>\n<p>1 May - May Day</p>\n<p>8 May - Liberation from Fascism</p>\n<p>5 July - Cyril and Methodius</p>\n<p>6 July - Burning at Stake of Jan Hus</p>\n<p>28 September - Czech Statehood Day</p>\n<p>28 October - Establishment of the Czechoslovak Republic</p>\n<p>17 November - Freedom and Democracy Day</p>\n<p>24 December - Christmas Eve</p>\n<p>25 December - Christmas Day</p>\n<p>26 December - Christmas Day</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Czech Republic Public Holidays for 2013:</p>\n<p>1 January - New Year''s Day</p>\n<p>1 April - Easter</p>\n<p>1 May - May Day</p>\n<p>8 May - Liberation from Fascism</p>\n<p>5 July - Cyril and Methodius</p>\n<p>6 July - Burning at Stake of Jan Hus</p>\n<p>28 September - Czech Statehood Day</p>\n<p>28 October - Establishment of the Czechoslovak Republic</p>\n<p>17 November - Freedom and Democracy Day</p>\n<p>24 December - Christmas Eve</p>\n<p>25 December - Christmas Day</p>\n<p>26 December - Christmas Day</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Customs"></a>Local Customs </strong></p>\n<p>It is a common courtesy to respect local customs. Drinking in public and drunken behaviour is punishable by law. Be polite!</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Vaccination"></a>Vaccination</strong></p>\n<p>There are no vaccination requirements for international travellers, and no major health risks are associated with travel to the Czech Republic. Visitors to forested areas should seek medical advice about immunisation against tick borne encephalitis.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Phrasebook"></a>Phrasebook</strong><strong> </strong></p>\n<p>Hello.&nbsp;- Dobr&yacute; den. (<em>DOH-bree dehn</em>)</p>\n<p>Hello. (<em>informal</em>)&nbsp;- Ahoj. (<em>ahoy</em>)</p>\n<p>How are you? (<em>formal</em>)- Jak se m&aacute;te? (<em>yahk seh MAA-teh?</em>)</p>\n<p>How are you? (<em>informal</em>)- Jak se m&aacute;&scaron;? (<em>yahk seh MAA-sh?</em>)</p>\n<p>Fine, thank you.&nbsp;- Dobře, děkuji. (<em>DOH-brzheh, DYEH-koo-yih.</em>)</p>\n<p>What is your name?&nbsp;- Jak se jmenuje&scaron;? (<em>yahk seh YMEH-noo-yehsh?</em>)</p>\n<p>My name is ______ .&nbsp;- Jmenuji se ______ . (<em>YMEH-noo-ee seh _____.</em>)</p>\n<p>Nice to meet you.&nbsp; - Tě&scaron;&iacute; mě. (<em>TYEH-shee myeh.</em>)</p>\n<p>Please.&nbsp;- Pros&iacute;m (<em>Proseem</em>)</p>\n<p>Thank you.&nbsp;- Děkuji. (<em>Dyekooyih.</em>)</p>\n<p>You''re welcome.&nbsp;- R&aacute;do se stalo. (<em>Raado seh stulo.</em>)</p>\n<p>Yes.&nbsp;- Ano. (<em>AH-noh.</em>)</p>\n<p>No.&nbsp;- Ne. (<em>neh.</em>)</p>\n<p>Excuse me, I am sorry. (<em>getting attention</em>)&nbsp; Promiňte (<em>PROH-mih-nyteh</em>)</p>\n<p>I''m sorry.&nbsp;- Je mi to l&iacute;to. (<em>yeh mee toh LEE-toh</em>)</p>\n<p>Goodbye&nbsp;- Na shledanou (<em>NAHSH-leh-dah-noh</em>)</p>\n<p>I can''t speak Czech [well].&nbsp;- Neum&iacute;m [moc dobře] mluvit česky (<em>Neh-oomeem [mots dobrzheh] mloovit cheskee.</em>)</p>\n<p>Do you speak English?&nbsp;- Mluv&iacute;te anglicky? (<em>Mlooveeteh unglitskee?</em>)</p>\n<p>Is there someone here who speaks English?&nbsp;- Je tady někdo, kdo mluv&iacute; anglicky? (<em>Yeh tuhdih nyegdo gdo mloovee uhnglitskee?</em>)</p>\n<p>Help!&nbsp;- Pomoc! (<em>POH-mohts!</em>)</p>\n<p>Look out!&nbsp;- Pozor! (<em>Pozor!</em>)</p>\n<p>I don''t understand.&nbsp;- Nerozum&iacute;m (<em>NEH-roh-zoo-meem</em>)</p>\n<p>Where is the toilet?&nbsp;- Kde je z&aacute;chod? (<em>Gdeh yeh ZAHH-khoht?</em>)</p>\n<p>Police!&nbsp;-&nbsp; Policie! (<em>POH-lee-tsee-eh!</em>)</p>\n<p>I need your help.&nbsp;- Potřebuji va&scaron;i pomoc. (<em>POHT-rzheh-boo-yee VAH-shee POH-mots</em>)</p>\n<p>It''s an emergency.&nbsp;- To je nebezpeč&iacute;. (<em>toh yeh NEH-behz-peh-chee</em>)</p>\n<p>I''m lost.&nbsp;- Jsem ztracen (<em>YEH-sehm ZTRAH-tsehn</em>)</p>\n<p>I''m sick. - Je mi &scaron;patně. (<em>yeh mee SHPAH-tnehh</em>)</p>\n<p>I''ve been injured.&nbsp;- Jsem zraněn (<em>YEH-sehm ZRAH-nehhn</em>)</p>\n<p>I need a doctor.&nbsp;- Potřebuji doktora (<em>POHT-rgeh-boo-yee DOHK-toh-rah</em>)</p>\n<p>Can I use your phone?&nbsp;- Mohu použ&iacute;t v&aacute;&scaron; telefon? (<em>MOH-hoo pwoh-zheet vaash TEH-leh-fohn?</em>)</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Time"></a>Time </strong></p>\n<p>Time Zone GMT (UTC) +1</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Visas"></a>Visas</strong></p>\n<p>Citizens of EU, Iceland, Norway, Liechtenstein and Switzerland do not require a visa to stay in the Czech Republic. However, notification obligation does apply for stays longer than 3 months. You must notify the pertinent inspectorate of the foreign police service.</p>\n<p>Citizens of other countries may require a visa to enter the Czech Republic. Please check entry requirements with Czech embassy or consular in your country.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Safety"></a>Safety</strong></p>\n<p>The Czech Republic is a safe European country but pickpocketing is not uncommon, like in any other EU country. Common sense is the best defense against petty crime. Keeping valuables in hotel safe&rsquo;s and avoiding small dark streets will make the trip more secure and trouble free.</p>\n<p>If you are the victim of theft, contact the police and your embassy (for replacement documents).</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Money"></a>Money </strong></p>\n<p>Although the Czech Republic is a member of the EU, it is not a member of the Eurozone. Official currency is Czech Koruna (CZK).</p>\n<p>It is very easy to exchange GBP, EURO or USD into Czech Koruna at the bank, hotel or bureau of exchange. And, of course, if you have an international bankcard you can withdraw Czech Krona from the bank machine.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Most hotels and some restaurants will accept payments by credit/debit card.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Exchange rate vary from place to place. As of April 2012, 1 EURO is approximately 25 CZK and 1 GBP is approximately 30 CZK.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Tipping"></a>Tipping </strong></p>\n<p>Tipping in bars and restaurants is optional and no service charge added to the bill. Gratuities 10% of the bill for those who have done a good job are a norm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Smoking"></a>Smoking </strong></p>\n<p>In the Czech Republic, you will find restaurants where smoking is permitted, completely non-smoking restaurants and also those that have separate rooms for non-smokers or there is a ban on smoking around noon in the restaurant.</p>\n<p><br /> There is a complete ban on smoking in enclosed areas freely accessible to the public, public transport, covered platforms, shelters and waiting rooms for public road and rail transport as well as public transport in cities.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Language"></a>Language </strong></p>\n<p>The official language is Czech. English and German are becoming widespread, especially in big cities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Spas and Hotels have staff that speaks English, German, Russian and other languages.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a name="Insurance2"></a>Insurance </strong></p>\n<p>EU citizens with a European Health Insurance Card (EHIC) are entitled to free essential emergency health care, however, on the basis of this card, the insurance company will not even cover the excess stipulated by the local laws such as: vsit to GP &ndash; 30CZK, emergency treatment &ndash; 90CZK, a day in hospital &ndash; 60CZK, item on prescription &ndash; 30 CZK, etc. Therefore a medical insurance that can cover all costs is advised.</p>\n<p>Non-EU citizens must have travel and medical insurance cover.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a name="Electricity"></a>Electricity</strong></p>\n<p>Voltage 230V, Frequency 50Hz. Electrical plugs with two round pins and a hole for the socket''s male grounding pin are standard. Most outlets will also accept standard European two-pin plugs.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, ''),
(3, 3, 1337596529, 1, 'Terms and Conditions', '<p><a name="Begining"></a>Please read the following conditions carefully since they set out the terms and conditions of the contract between you and Digital Aurum Ltd, trading as czechspaholidays.com (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, &ldquo;our&rdquo; or &ldquo;ourselves&rdquo;).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="#Privacy"><strong>Privacy and Security Policy </strong></a></p>\n<p><strong><a href="#Booking">Booking Conditions</a><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><strong><br /></strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong><strong><br /></strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong><strong><a name="Privacy"></a><span style="font-size: medium;">Privacy and Security Policy</span></strong></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>1. Introduction</strong></p>\n<p>Thank you for visiting Czech Spa Holidays.com. This privacy policy tells you how we use personal information collected on our website. Please read this privacy policy before using the site or submitting any personal information. By using the site, you are accepting the practices described in this privacy policy. These practices may be changed, but any changes will be posted and changes will only apply to activities and information on a going forward, not retroactive basis. You are encouraged to review the privacy policy whenever you visit the site to make sure that you understand how any personal information you provide will be used.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>2. Collection of Information</strong><strong><br /> </strong>2.1 When you make an online booking, we collect personally identifiable information such as your name, billing address, and other contact details. We need all this information to process your order and to be able to contact you when more information is needed or if there are any changes to the programme.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2.2 Additional personal information maybe given by you when you communicate with us about status of your booking and/or when sending a feedback about our service.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2.3 We may store your personal information including your booking details.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2.4 We do not store your credit/debit card information.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>3. Use of Information</strong></p>\n<p>3.1 The information you provide is used for internal record keeping, processing your booking and contacting you if more information is needed or if there are any changes to the programme.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>3.2 We may also use the information to improve our services and to periodically send promotional emails about new products, special offers or other information that we think you may find interesting.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>4. Commitment to Data Security</strong></p>\n<p>4.1 Your personally identifiable information is kept secure. In order to prevent unauthorised access or disclosure, we have put in place suitable physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect on this website.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>5. How we use cookies</strong></p>\n<p>5.1 A cookie is a small file which asks permission to be placed on your computer''s hard drive. Once you agree, the file is added and the cookie helps analyse web traffic or lets you know when you visit a particular site. Cookies allow web applications to respond to you as an individual. The web application can tailor its operations to your needs, likes and dislikes by gathering and remembering information about your preferences.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5.2 We use traffic log cookies to identify which pages are being used. This helps us analyse data about webpage traffic and improve our website in order to tailor it to customer needs. We only use this information for statistical analysis purposes and then the data is removed from the system.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5.3 Overall, cookies help us provide you with a better website by enabling us to monitor which pages you find useful and which you do not. A cookie in no way gives us access to your computer or any information about you, other than the data you choose to share with us.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5.4 You can choose to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. This may prevent you from taking full advantage of the website.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>6. Distribution of Information&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><br /> 6.1 We will not sell, distribute or lease your personal information to third parties.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>6.2 We may share information with governmental agencies or other companies assisting us in fraud prevention or investigation. We may do so when:</p>\n<p>(1) permitted or required by law; or,</p>\n<p>(2) trying to protect against or prevent actual or potential fraud or unauthorized transactions; or,</p>\n<p>(3) investigating fraud which has already taken place.</p>\n<p>The information is not provided to these companies for marketing purposes.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>7. Links to other websites</strong></p>\n<p>7.1 Our website may contain links to other websites of interest. However, once you have used these links to leave our site, you should note that we do not have any control over that other website. Therefore, we cannot be responsible for the protection and privacy of any information which you provide whilst visiting such sites and such sites are not governed by this privacy statement. You should exercise caution and look at the privacy statement applicable to the website in question.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>8. Accessing and rectifying your personal data:</strong></p>\n<p>8.1 You may request details of personal information that we hold about you under the Data Protection Act 1998. A small fee will be payable.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>8.2 If you believe that any information we are holding on you is incorrect or incomplete, please write to or email us using the details provided on our website. We will swiftly correct any information found to be incorrect.</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>9. Privacy Contact Information</strong><br /> 9.1 If you have any questions, concerns, or comments about our privacy policy you may contact us using contact information provided on our website.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="#Begining">Back to the top</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong><a name="Booking"></a>Booking Conditions</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>1. Formation of the contact</strong></p>\n<p>1.1 By making a booking on czechspaholidays.com you agree to be bound by these bookings conditions. A binding contract will come into effect between you and us when we have sent you a booking confirmation and an invoice, whether you received it or not.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>2. Pricing </strong></p>\n<p>2.1 All prices shown on our website are in EUR with equivalent in other currently using mid-market rates.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2.2 All sales are finalized in EUR regardless of any other currency being displayed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2.3 Prices are subject to change without notice, however, we make every effort to ensure prices are correct and up to date at the time of publishing.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>3. Payment</strong></p>\n<p>3.1 To guarantee your booking, payment in full is required. However, in some exceptional cases, we will accept a non-refundable deposit of 15% with a balance payable no later than 10 weeks prior to departure date. Please phone our office to discuss.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>3.2 We accept payments by credit/debit cards, cheques and bank transfers. It is not possible to pay by cash.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>3.3 When making an online booking, your card will not be debited until all services have been confirmed. Your card/bank statement will show that monies were paid to Digital Aurum Ltd.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>4. Changes and cancellations by You. &nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>4.1 Should you wish to make any changes to your confirmed booking, you must notify us by email as soon as possible. We will do our best to make the change, however it may not always be possible. Changes are subject to administration fee of 25 GBP per booking and payment of any price difference incurred as a result of change. It will not be possible to make any changes to your booking within 72 hours prior to check in date.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>4.2 Should you need to cancel your stay once it has been confirmed, you must notify us by email as soon as possible. If you cancel your bookings more than 14 days before the arrival date we will refund you full amount minus 25% cancellation fee.</p>\n<p>If you cancel your booking within 13 &ndash; 3 days before the arrival date we will refund you full amount minus 50% cancellation fee.</p>\n<p>If you cancel your booking within 72 hours before the arrival date no claim for any refund can be accepted.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>5. Changes and cancellations by us. </strong></p>\n<p>5.1Whilst we always endeavour to avoid changes and cancellations, we must reserve the right to do so.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5.2 During busy periods hotels receive high volume of requests and may not be able to confirm your bookings. In such event we will notify you as soon as possible (no later than 72 hours after you made your reservation) and will offer alternative arrangements or your money back, whichever suits best.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5.3 Once we confirmed your booking this will not be subject to change or cancellation unless circumstances beyond our control. Circumstances beyond our control include, but are not limited to, acts of god and the inability of a provider to fulfil its commitment. In the case of the latter example, we will provide equivalent or better service/product or a full refund.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>6. Disclaimer</strong></p>\n<p>6.1 Subject to the limitations set out in these terms and conditions and to the extent permitted by law, we shall only be liable for direct damages actually suffered, paid or incurred by you due to an attributable shortcoming of our obligations in respect to our services, up to an aggregate amount of the aggregate cost of your reservation as set out in the confirmation email (whether for one event or series of connected events).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>6.2 However and to the extent permitted by law, neither we nor any of our officers, directors, employees, representatives, subsidiaries, affiliated companies, distributors, affiliate (distribution) partners, licensees, agents or others involved in creating, sponsoring, promoting, or otherwise making available the site and its contents shall be liable for (i) any punitive, special, indirect or consequential loss or damages, any loss of production, loss of profit, loss of revenue, loss of contract, loss of or damage to goodwill or reputation, loss of claim, (ii) any inaccuracy relating to the (descriptive) information (including rates, availability and ratings) of the hotel as made available on our website, (iii) the services rendered or the products offered by the hotel, (iv) any (direct, indirect, consequential or punitive) damages, losses or costs suffered, incurred or paid by you, pursuant to, arising out of or in connection with the use, inability to use or delay of our website, or (v) for any (personal) injury, death, property damage, or other (direct, indirect, special, consequential or punitive) damages, losses or costs suffered, incurred or paid by you, whether due to (legal) acts, errors, breaches, (gross) negligence, willful misconduct, omissions, non-performance, misrepresentations, tort or strict liability by or (wholly or partly) attributable to the hotel (its employees, directors, officers, agents, representatives or affiliated companies), including any (partial) cancellation, overbooking, strike, force majeure or any other event beyond our control.</p>\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>7. Website Accuracy </strong></p>\n<p>7.1 While we make every reasonable efforts to ensure that programmes and hotels descriptions (including star rating, photos, treatments and facilities information) supplied by owners are accurately reproduced on our website we do not accept responsibility for any descriptions which contain inaccurate, incomplete or misleading information.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>7.2 If we have been informed of changes to the transportation, property, treatment, etc we will ensure that our website is updated to reflect the new information. If we have been informed of material changes to your programme after your booking has been confirmed we will advise you before departure.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>7.3 Differences between photographs and text and actual property/arrangements may occur.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>8. Special Requirements </strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>8.1 All special requests should be submitted at the time of booking. We will pass your special request to the relevant Spa resort. Please note that all requests are on request-only basis and can not be guaranteed even if they are printed on your voucher.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>9. English Law and Jurisdiction</strong> <br /> 9.1 This agreement is governed by English law and is subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England &amp; Wales.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Terms and Conditions', '', NULL, NULL, ''),
(4, 0, 1337596880, 1, 'Work with Us', '<p>We are constantly looking for energetic, dynamic, people to join our team. So if you''re passionate about travel, committed to providing great customer service or skilled in any of the areas we rely upon (such as travel reservations, website development, content update, contracts, etc) we''d love to hear from you. Please email <a href="mailto:alyona@czechspaholidays.com">alyona@czechspaholidays.com</a></p>', 'work with us', '', NULL, NULL, ''),
(5, 1, 1337597735, 1, 'Contact Us', '<p><strong>We are always happy to hear from our potential clients!</strong><br /> <br /> If you''d like to get in touch with us to discuss the services we can offer you, please find our contact information below.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Czech Spa Holidays.com, trading Name of Digital Aurum Ltd, Registered in England and Wales No 7125426.</p>\n<p>Address: 21 Davidson Road, London, CR0 6DL, United Kingdom</p>\n<p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:alyona@czechspaholidays.com">alyona@czechspaholidays.com</a></p>\n<p>Tel: +44 (0)20 3468 1030</p>', 'contact us', '', NULL, NULL, ''),
(6, 1, 1337632654, 1, 'About Us', '<p>Welcome to Czech Spa Holidays &ndash; your specialist travel agent when organizing health and beauty holidays in mineral spring spas of the Czech Republic.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Why book your health and beauty holidays to the Czech Republic with us:</p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>We know what we offer: </strong>we are a dynamic, professional team passionate about the Czech Republic, its rich culture, history and most of all its natural healing recourses. We have acquired extensive knowledge of the programmes we offer and built strong relationships with our suppliers, so you can benefit from expert&rsquo;s advice.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>We deliver: </strong>we understand that when you book your holiday with us you trust us to deliver. &nbsp;Our team works hard to ensure that your experience with us is one of supreme excellence in quality, service and value.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Saving you time:</strong> our aim is to offer a one-stop shop with <strong>all</strong> Spa &amp; Wellness, Health &amp; Beauty programmes in the Czech Republic. So if you are looking for a specific treatment, want to improve your over all health, or simply would like to have a beauty and relaxation programme &ndash; you do not have to look anywhere else; you will find it here.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Value for money:</strong> we maintain good relationships and direct contracts with spa suppliers in the Czech Republic and ensure that we pass on to you the best deals and offers.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Easy to chose:</strong> our intuitive, easy-to-use website allows you to navigate, and choose your programme in 3 easy steps.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Easy to book:</strong> our advanced reservation system allows you to book your programme in 2 easy steps.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Security: </strong>we offer secure online payment method<strong>.</strong> Money accepted only when the booking is fully confirmed by the supplier.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Looking after you.</strong> Our team will support you before, during and after your holiday.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>We are looking forward to booking your Health and Beauty Holidays in the Czech Republic for you!</strong></p>', 'About Us', '', NULL, NULL, ''),
(7, 0, 1337632762, 1, 'Useful Links', '<p>Comming Soon...</p>', 'Useful Links', '', NULL, NULL, '');
